\m Up to 1,000 verses of this work may be quoted in non-saleable media such as church bulletins, newsletters, orders of service and teaching material without the need for written permission. For other uses please contact Wycliffe Bible Translators Australia. To use pictures included in this Bible, please contact the respective copyright holders.
\b
\m The artwork on the cover is by Andrew Wanimilil Malibirr, from Ramingining. Used with permission.
\m The whole artwork, in the shape of a cross, is a picture of Jesus’s sacrifice. The bit in the middle represents the Last Supper, with Jesus and his disciples sitting around a fire, symbolic of the Holy Spirit. The cross hatching is a symbol of the water and blood that flowed out of Jesus’s body. And the small dots are from the Ganalbingu people’s story of the flying fox, and here represent Jesus’s blood taking away the sin of the world. The picture uses art styles from Arnhem Land and Central Australia, reminding us that Jesus’s story is for everyone.
\b
\m Other illustration acknowledgements are on page ###.
\b
\m ISBN 978-0-XXXX
